Section 1: Practical Technical Assessment
Time Allowed: 60 Minutes

1. Database Schema Design

Write PL/SQL dynamic code to create a table that includes the following fields: Name, Joining Date, Manager Name, Salary, and Commission.

Create a trigger to automatically generate ID column values whenever a new record is inserted into this table.

2. Data Manipulation

Develop one or more stored procedures to insert data into the table you created.

Manually insert at least 5 sample records using your procedures.

3. Oracle Forms Development

Build one or more data entry forms for the table, preferably using a Master-Detail design.

Implement a warning message that must be displayed to the user before a form record is saved.


General & Project Background

Q1: Tell about yourself.

Q2: Regarding your project, how many entry forms and Master-Detail forms are there?.

Q3: Are your setup forms single entry forms?.

Q4: How will a user know if an item purchase is required?.

Q5: Why did everyone work on the same project?.

Technical Architecture & Tools

Q6: Explain the different types of trigger levels available in Form Builder.

Q7: Identify specific triggers available at each level and name them.

Q8: How many types of triggers are in Report Builder? Please list their names.

Q9: What are the primary differences between Developer Suite and Oracle APEX?.

SQL & Reporting

Q10: Provide details on the different types of SQL Joins.

Q11: What specific Reports were utilized in your project?.

Q12: Provide details regarding the company you are interviewing for.